                            <comment id="12881164" author="lukakama" created="Tue, 22 Jun 2010 11:01:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching sample PDF and it&apos;s image conversion&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12881802" author="lehmi" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2010 18:18:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Version 957289 provides a solution for documents with portrait orientation. Do you have a similar example with landscape orientation?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12882086" author="lukakama" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2010 08:22:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching a landscape sample. &lt;br/&gt;
I don&apos;t know why i got a portrait image from the landscape pdf... &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The image was generated with version 957289. However.. I noticed that this version doesn&apos;t handle PNG images (in a first attempt i got blank images), so i&apos;ve used a jpeg version. Souldn&apos;t PNG works with 1.2.0 snapshot?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12882123" author="lukakama" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2010 10:50:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, found another problem: when images are rotated and resized without an aspect ration of 1:1, their continue to be misplaced or rendered incorrectly (see top-right image has an height smaller then the PDF original)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13011435" author="lehmi" created="Fri, 25 Mar 2011 21:37:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I fixed the issue in revision 1085566&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
